The thorny issue of land expropriation without
compensation is here and it looks like it's going to dominate debates for quite
some time. Soon after the ANC supported the EFF's motion on land
expropriation without compensation, South Africa's opinion on the matter was
split into two.Some are for the idea while other are against it. And of
course, each grouping has its own 'reasonable' reasons.  The EFF's motion
calls for the constitution to be amended in favour of land expropriation
